dcterms:description: OpenAI Gym is a toolkit for developing and comparing reinforcement learning algorithms, providing a variety of environments to test and train agents.
dcterms:title: OpenAI Gym

dcterms:description: The Pendulum dataset is used to model the dynamics of a pendulum system, typically involving the angle and angular velocity as state variables.
dcterms:title: Pendulum

dcterms:description: The CartPole dataset is used to model the dynamics of a cart-pole system, where the goal is to balance the pole on the cart by applying forces.
dcterms:title: CartPole

dcterms:description: The Acrobot dataset is used to model the dynamics of a two-link robotic arm, where the objective is to swing the end of the arm to a target position.
dcterms:title: Acrobot

dcterms:description: Hamiltonian Generative Networks (HGN) learn Hamiltonian dynamics from image sequences, providing a framework for modeling physical systems.
dcterms:title: HGN (Hamiltonian Generative Networks)

dcterms:description: Hamiltonian Neural Networks (PixelHNN) learn Hamiltonian dynamics from position, velocity, and acceleration data, focusing on the integration of physics into neural networks.
dcterms:title: PixelHNN (Hamiltonian Neural Networks)
